1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,799
[moody, intense intro music plays]

2
00:01:01,979 --> 00:01:05,983
THE GLORY

3
00:01:06,066 --> 00:01:07,776
[panting]

4
00:01:12,948 --> 00:01:14,616
[Myeong-o grunting]

5
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:16,702
[delicate, mysterious music playing]

6
00:01:20,122 --> 00:01:20,998
[Yeon-jin screams]

7
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:24,042
[Yeon-jin gasps]

8
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:28,130
[blood gurgling]

9
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:32,092
[Myeong-o gasping for breath]

10
00:01:38,015 --> 00:01:39,975
[sinister music builds]

11
00:01:44,187 --> 00:01:47,190
[Yeon-jin whimpering]

12
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:05,834
[Yeon-jin] Hey.

13
00:02:09,212 --> 00:02:10,464
Shit. Fuck.

14
00:03:07,396 --> 00:03:08,814
[mover] One, two, three.

15
00:03:08,897 --> 00:03:11,191
[Yeong-jun]
<i>She'll take care of the cameras,</i>

16
00:03:11,274 --> 00:03:14,611
<i>so just make sure</i>
<i>nothing's left at the scene.</i>

17
00:03:22,119 --> 00:03:23,328
SLIDE TO POWER OFF

18
00:03:30,252 --> 00:03:33,964
OUT OF BUSINESS
DO NOT ENTER

19
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:38,176
YEONGSAN FUNERAL HOME

20
00:04:04,745 --> 00:04:05,746
[phone trills]

21
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:07,122
[line ringing]

22
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:11,960
It's me.

23
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:14,296
He scratched me on the foot.

24
00:04:15,213 --> 00:04:17,674
Okay, don't worry. I've got this covered.

25
00:04:17,758 --> 00:04:19,301
[Yeon-jin breathing heavily]

26
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:21,011
<i>What are you going to do?</i>

27
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:24,639
[Yeong-jun] I'll bury him.
That's the best way to take care of it.

28
00:04:24,723 --> 00:04:25,891
<i>I'll call you later.</i>

29
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:33,982
[mover] You want to bury him now?
Sun's up soon.

30
00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:35,400
No, we can't do it today.

31
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:39,279
We'll wait until it rains,
so everything's contaminated.

32
00:04:43,742 --> 00:04:44,743
Hey.

33
00:04:47,704 --> 00:04:48,872
Stop for a second.

34
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:50,957
[tense, cryptic music playing]

35
00:05:03,178 --> 00:05:05,263
MORTUARY

36
00:05:07,349 --> 00:05:09,518
-[breaker tripping]
-[Yeon-jin gasps]

37
00:05:13,647 --> 00:05:15,774
[Yeo-jeong] How did you sleep, Ms. Park?

38
00:05:16,775 --> 00:05:18,360
[breathing shakily]

39
00:05:20,195 --> 00:05:22,197
[menacing music playing]

40
00:05:27,536 --> 00:05:31,039
Looks like you were having a nightmare.
You can lie down before you go.

41
00:05:31,122 --> 00:05:34,167
Who are you?
What the hell did you just do?

42
00:05:34,751 --> 00:05:36,336
Where's the security camera?

43
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:39,005
-Oh, are you all right?
-Let go of me!

44
00:05:39,089 --> 00:05:42,425
Show me now!
What did you do to me while I was asleep?

45
00:05:42,509 --> 00:05:43,426
What did you do?!

46
00:05:44,886 --> 00:05:47,931
Ma'am, there are no security cameras
in the operating room.

47
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,766
I think you're feeling confused

48
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:51,601
because the anesthesia
hasn't worn off yet.

49
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:53,562
Could you explain
how you're feeling right now?

50
00:05:53,645 --> 00:05:54,896
[medical monitor beeping wildly]

51
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:57,315
[nurse] Her blood pressure
and pulse were both normal.

52
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:59,359
Ms. Park! You shouldn't be driving yet!

53
00:06:02,988 --> 00:06:03,989
[monitor beeps]

54
00:06:04,072 --> 00:06:06,074
[dark, threatening music plays]

55
00:06:07,909 --> 00:06:09,911
[Yeon-jin panting]

56
00:06:35,478 --> 00:06:40,483
THE GLORY

57
00:06:42,819 --> 00:06:44,487
I had so many questions.

58
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,491
They're pointless now.

59
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:51,828
Do those still cause you pain?

60
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:54,331
Don't ask me that.

61
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:58,418
I don't want to hear lame questions.

62
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,588
Even if this is all pointless,

63
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:03,715
there's something more important
for you to ask now.

64
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:06,760
"Did Yeon-jin really do it?"

65
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:17,062
So, did you look for Myeong-o?
I even sent you a picture.

66
00:07:17,145 --> 00:07:19,230
[elegant classical music playing faintly]

67
00:07:21,942 --> 00:07:23,526
Anything else I need to know?

68
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:27,405
You know enough to leave Yeon-jin.
What else could you need to hear?

69
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:30,325
Listen.

70
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:31,826
To be transparent,

71
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:34,871
I want everyone in her life to leave her.

72
00:07:34,955 --> 00:07:36,039
Including you.

73
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:38,375
Why?

74
00:07:39,376 --> 00:07:41,795
Because you're Yeon-jin's glory.
Don't you agree?

75
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,881
But after all of this,

76
00:07:45,632 --> 00:07:48,134
I want you to become
another reminder of Yeon-jin's ruin.

77
00:07:52,389 --> 00:07:54,140
With a plan like this,

78
00:07:55,225 --> 00:07:57,310
I'm surprised you weren't more proactive.

79
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:00,480
You aren't that aggressive.

80
00:08:00,563 --> 00:08:02,565
[somber music playing]

81
00:08:07,779 --> 00:08:09,531
I'm not going to leave her.

82
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:13,827
Why not?

83
00:08:15,078 --> 00:08:16,079
I don't know.

84
00:08:17,747 --> 00:08:19,416
I don't like admitting it either,

85
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:21,668
but I really don't.

86
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:28,216
I only realized
I'm not going to leave Yeon-jin right now.

87
00:08:32,053 --> 00:08:33,054
So, maybe…

88
00:08:36,891 --> 00:08:38,018
we should meet again.

89
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:47,610
[steady tapping]

90
00:09:01,124 --> 00:09:03,126
Go sleep. It'll be 20 minutes.

91
00:09:08,757 --> 00:09:11,676
I haven't eaten either.
I'll wake you up for it.

92
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:15,722
I'm awake.
What you're cooking smells so good.

93
00:09:17,682 --> 00:09:19,017
Is there some for me?

94
00:09:19,517 --> 00:09:20,685
It's amazing, right?

95
00:09:20,769 --> 00:09:23,271
Oh! Park Yeon-jin came
and got the procedure.

96
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:25,315
And I just met with Ha Do-yeong.

97
00:09:26,483 --> 00:09:29,110
I'm a terrible cook,
but at least let me help.

98
00:09:29,194 --> 00:09:30,904
I can still follow directions.

99
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:39,829
[Yeo-jeong] Ah!

100
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:42,123
It's hot.

101
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:43,583
You'll get hurt.

102
00:09:46,294 --> 00:09:50,048
I'm so used to them, but I guess my scars
can be hard for people to look at.

103
00:09:51,508 --> 00:09:52,675
It's not that at all.

104
00:09:53,635 --> 00:09:55,887
Why did you dress up so nicely
to go to see Ha Do-yeong?

105
00:09:55,970 --> 00:09:58,098
You could have just gone in your sweats.

106
00:09:58,181 --> 00:09:59,808
Your face says that.

107
00:09:59,891 --> 00:10:00,892
[chuckles softly]

108
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:03,103
It was just cold today.

109
00:10:05,396 --> 00:10:06,898
Call me over when you're done.

110
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:09,109
I didn't even get a chance
to wash my face.

111
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:12,737
[Yeo-jeong] Let me heal you.

112
00:10:18,743 --> 00:10:21,162
Starting with the wounds
closest to your wrists,

113
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:24,457
and then working on the ones
closest to your ankles.

114
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,085
It'd be pointless.

115
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:28,586
It wouldn't be that.

116
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:33,550
An old wound can only heal and recover
by making a new, deeper cut.

117
00:10:34,217 --> 00:10:36,469
The fresh cut will repair the tissue.

118
00:10:36,553 --> 00:10:38,555
I'll make the cuts for you.

119
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:42,934
You might not go back
to what you were before,

120
00:10:43,017 --> 00:10:44,269
but you can get close.

121
00:10:48,148 --> 00:10:51,568
It's pointless,
because I'm not in pain now.

122
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:01,786
[pot simmering, rattling]

123
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:08,751
[woman] <i>Sun-a did an excellent job</i>
<i>with the interview at the embassy.</i>

124
00:11:08,835 --> 00:11:10,503
<i>You can send the agency fee</i>

125
00:11:10,587 --> 00:11:13,381
<i>and buy her plane ticket</i>
<i>for the date she's to leave.</i>

126
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:18,178
Thank you so much.
Please text me the account number.

127
00:11:23,141 --> 00:11:25,018
[chuckling]

128
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:33,985
[sighs heavily]

129
00:11:35,236 --> 00:11:36,863
Who's got the prettiest "V"?

130
00:11:37,447 --> 00:11:39,157
Oh, you're all so pretty.

131
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,659
All right, let's go to the jungle gym.
Come on.

132
00:11:41,743 --> 00:11:43,244
[kids clamoring happily]

133
00:11:43,328 --> 00:11:45,788
[Mr. Chu] Okay, be careful.
Careful, careful.

134
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:48,166
-[shutter snaps]
-Careful. Okay.

135
00:12:10,605 --> 00:12:12,607
[dark, foreboding music playing]

136
00:12:18,529 --> 00:12:20,698
-[doorbell rings]
-[Seong-hee] <i>I have a package for you.</i>

137
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:23,493
-A package?
-[Seong-hee] Yeah.

138
00:12:26,371 --> 00:12:28,456
I'm not waiting for any packages.

139
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:32,794
It's for you to feel better.

140
00:12:33,795 --> 00:12:35,588
Dong-eun sent this to you.

141
00:12:37,006 --> 00:12:38,675
[gentle, heartfelt music playing]

142
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:58,653
[Dong-eun] <i>They picked</i>
<i>a home-stay family for Sun-a.</i>

143
00:12:58,736 --> 00:13:01,281
<i>If you want to say anything to them,</i>
<i>write it down.</i>

144
00:13:01,364 --> 00:13:04,033
<i>Write it in Korean.</i>
<i>I'll translate it for you.</i>

145
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:06,119
"Laura Willson."

146
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:09,372
<i>I sent the lipstick</i>

147
00:13:09,956 --> 00:13:12,083
<i>because I think it will look good on you.</i>

148
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,046
[disbelieving chuckle]

149
00:13:20,383 --> 00:13:23,052
<i>From now on,</i>
<i>I'll contact you through Sun-a's phone.</i>

150
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:28,516
[music trails off]

151
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:34,230
[nun] Our mother came back from praying
at Gyeryongsan. She prayed over this food.

152
00:13:34,314 --> 00:13:37,567
Oh, wow! Thank you so much for this gift.

153
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,736
I'll be sure to savor every bite.

154
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:41,446
[phone ringing]

155
00:13:41,529 --> 00:13:43,406
JOO GENERAL HOSPITAL EMPLOYEE

156
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:44,991
Excuse me.

157
00:13:48,411 --> 00:13:49,412
Yes, hello?

158
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:50,496
SEOUL JOO GENERAL HOSPITAL

159
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:52,373
[Yeon-jin's mother]
What are you talking about?

160
00:13:52,457 --> 00:13:55,376
Why is the director's son
looking for Yoon So-hee's body?

161
00:13:55,877 --> 00:13:58,546
I have no idea why.
Trying to inherit the hospital?

162
00:14:01,174 --> 00:14:03,092
But you know what's even weirder?

163
00:14:03,176 --> 00:14:06,262
The body is in the freezer
instead of the morgue.

164
00:14:06,346 --> 00:14:08,806
The freezer? Why would it be in there?

165
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:10,725
I don't know any of the details.

166
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:14,896
I think I'm too scared to do this anymore,
between you and that visitor…

167
00:14:14,979 --> 00:14:16,898
Visitor? Someone from her family?

168
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:19,859
No. Son Myeong-o.
He said he was her friend.

169
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:21,069
-Myeong-o?
-Uh-huh.

170
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,280
Why would he do that?

171
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:30,453
What's happening?
What the hell is going on here?

172
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:39,796
[Yeo-jeong] <i>Son Myeong-o.</i>
<i>What did you do to him?</i>

173
00:14:41,798 --> 00:14:43,466
Did he actually ask that?

174
00:14:45,051 --> 00:14:46,386
Maybe not. Shit.

175
00:14:51,974 --> 00:14:52,975
[knocking at window]

176
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:04,529
Oh, it is you. Hello there.

177
00:15:06,364 --> 00:15:08,533
Are you here for your retouching?
It's not today.

178
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:10,660
Uh, no, I was going there.

179
00:15:10,743 --> 00:15:11,869
Ah.

180
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:15,665
I'm so sorry, Doctor.
I guess I was out of it.

181
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:21,712
Did I, uh, say weird things
to you that day?

182
00:15:23,089 --> 00:15:24,132
Oh.

183
00:15:27,593 --> 00:15:28,511
Son Myeong-o?

184
00:15:28,594 --> 00:15:30,263
[suspenseful stinger]

185
00:15:31,389 --> 00:15:33,182
You said that name several times that day.

186
00:15:36,144 --> 00:15:38,896
But that's normal
when the anesthesia hasn't worn off.

187
00:15:38,980 --> 00:15:41,899
They usually come from somewhere
between dream and fantasy.

188
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:43,609
Oh, right.

189
00:15:44,569 --> 00:15:46,404
I actually had a really bad dream.

190
00:15:46,487 --> 00:15:48,531
That can happen when you're tired.

191
00:15:48,614 --> 00:15:51,200
Take your vitamins, okay?
I'll see you soon.

192
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:14,432
[Yeon-jin] <i>You should eat at home tonight.</i>
<i>I'm going to make crab stew.</i>

193
00:16:15,057 --> 00:16:16,976
<i>I won't be there, so it's safe, okay?</i>

194
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:32,200
Why are you eating now?

195
00:16:33,034 --> 00:16:34,243
Didn't you see my text?

196
00:16:35,036 --> 00:16:35,870
I saw it.

197
00:16:36,871 --> 00:16:38,289
Why didn't you say anything?

198
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:40,500
That is my response.

199
00:16:49,342 --> 00:16:52,178
Do you play Go with Moon Dong-eun? Do you?

200
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:54,597
What the hell are you doing?!

201
00:16:55,223 --> 00:16:56,974
I just don't understand.

202
00:16:57,475 --> 00:17:00,436
How could somebody like Dong-eun
even manage to catch your attention?

203
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:03,856
She made me curious when we met.

204
00:17:04,899 --> 00:17:06,859
I found myself always waiting for her.

205
00:17:06,943 --> 00:17:08,319
[intricate, somber music plays]

206
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:10,821
And when I met her again,
I wanted to beat her.

207
00:17:12,657 --> 00:17:14,867
But I lost the upper hand and floundered,

208
00:17:15,535 --> 00:17:16,869
because I was cornered.

209
00:17:18,371 --> 00:17:20,289
But part of me even wanted that, too.

210
00:17:21,624 --> 00:17:24,252
I liked it when she cornered me
in a Go match.

211
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:30,466
You cheated on me.

212
00:17:33,553 --> 00:17:35,763
No matter how you phrase it,
that's cheating.

213
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:37,598
[scoffs]

214
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:44,772
Seems unfair coming from you,
but all right, then.

215
00:17:46,315 --> 00:17:48,568
I'm not asking about
you and Jae-jun, am I?

216
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:57,577
You're not coming to the airport, are you?

217
00:17:59,245 --> 00:18:00,288
Neither is Mom?

218
00:18:05,418 --> 00:18:06,586
It's all right.

219
00:18:07,962 --> 00:18:09,213
I'll be okay on my own.

220
00:18:11,173 --> 00:18:12,008
Okay.

221
00:18:13,843 --> 00:18:15,761
Thank you for helping me run away.

222
00:18:16,554 --> 00:18:18,514
And thanks for giving me
a new life, Ms. Moon.

223
00:18:19,181 --> 00:18:21,601
It's not running away. There's hope now.

224
00:18:22,685 --> 00:18:23,603
Have fun too.

225
00:18:26,314 --> 00:18:30,318
I'll go to all the museums.
I swear I'll be a good person.

226
00:18:32,153 --> 00:18:33,487
I'm gonna become someone

227
00:18:34,155 --> 00:18:37,491
who has the ability to change
people's lives, just like you do.

228
00:18:39,619 --> 00:18:40,870
That's a good dream.

229
00:18:43,497 --> 00:18:45,416
But you don't want to be like me.

230
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:48,377
I'm not a good person.

231
00:18:50,087 --> 00:18:51,922
[Sun-a breathing tremulously]

232
00:18:58,596 --> 00:19:00,181
MYEONG-O

233
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:03,017
OCTOBER 14
HEY, TAE-UK'S EX-WIFE!

234
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:04,435
HOW MUCH LONGER?

235
00:19:08,481 --> 00:19:09,649
[Hye-jeong] <i>Are you in Russia?</i>

236
00:19:09,732 --> 00:19:13,319
<i>Hey, just tell me, did Dong-eun</i>
<i>do something to fuck with you, too?</i>

237
00:19:15,029 --> 00:19:16,489
This is going nowhere.

238
00:19:17,239 --> 00:19:18,908
I need a hint or something.

239
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:24,872
Oh, the tablet.

240
00:19:30,336 --> 00:19:31,253
Excuse me.

241
00:19:33,214 --> 00:19:35,383
There should be a tablet
right behind the passenger seat.

242
00:19:35,466 --> 00:19:36,550
Could you get that for me?

243
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:38,511
And who are you?

244
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:39,929
I'm Jae-jun's girlfriend.

245
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:41,180
Oh, you're his…

246
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:45,184
I know Mr. Jeon's girlfriends
because I've driven them,

247
00:19:45,768 --> 00:19:46,977
but I've never seen you.

248
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:50,147
Jae-jun is dating a redhead now, right?

249
00:19:50,231 --> 00:19:51,065
JAE-JUN

250
00:19:51,148 --> 00:19:52,692
