00:36:13,213 --> 00:36:14,214
[wry chuckle]

501
00:36:15,507 --> 00:36:16,341
You're crazy.

502
00:36:17,092 --> 00:36:17,926
What?

503
00:36:19,010 --> 00:36:23,056
[man] I checked your paperwork,
and in about… Oh, I had it. Here it is…

504
00:36:23,139 --> 00:36:23,973
A week or so,

505
00:36:24,057 --> 00:36:26,685
the real estate registration
will be available.

506
00:36:26,768 --> 00:36:27,602
All right.

507
00:36:29,396 --> 00:36:33,233
I don't mean to pry, but why would you
want to buy an abandoned funeral home?

508
00:36:33,316 --> 00:36:35,026
Are you trying to renovate, or…

509
00:36:36,027 --> 00:36:37,737
If you really want chocolate, sir,

510
00:36:37,821 --> 00:36:40,490
then you need to buy the box
the chocolate comes in.

511
00:36:40,990 --> 00:36:41,908
It's kind of like that.

512
00:36:43,284 --> 00:36:44,536
Ah, I see.

513
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:46,037
[chuckles]

514
00:36:46,121 --> 00:36:48,289
It's been on the market for quite a while.

515
00:36:48,373 --> 00:36:51,209
-You bought it for a very good price.
-Thank you so much.

516
00:37:08,143 --> 00:37:09,144
[phone buzzing]

517
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:16,067
[Sun-a] <i>Hi, Mom. I got here safely.</i>

518
00:37:17,819 --> 00:37:21,114
<i>I thought you might have my phone</i>
<i>and be able to read this.</i>

519
00:37:21,197 --> 00:37:23,908
<i>I waited for you at the airport</i>
<i>for a really long time.</i>

520
00:37:24,409 --> 00:37:26,703
<i>I'm sad I didn't see you before I left,</i>

521
00:37:26,786 --> 00:37:28,246
<i>but I'll be waiting for you,</i>

522
00:37:28,747 --> 00:37:30,582
<i>because I know you'll join me soon.</i>

523
00:37:31,332 --> 00:37:32,167
<i>I love you, Mom.</i>

524
00:37:32,250 --> 00:37:33,918
[low, keening wail]

525
00:37:34,002 --> 00:37:36,045
[Sun-a, emotionally] <i>I love you so much.</i>

526
00:37:36,671 --> 00:37:38,465
[Hyeon-nam sobbing]

527
00:37:47,182 --> 00:37:48,308
[bottles clinking]

528
00:37:48,391 --> 00:37:49,559
[Seok-jae humming]

529
00:37:52,395 --> 00:37:55,356
[tense, cryptic music playing]

530
00:38:08,411 --> 00:38:09,537
[phone buzzing]

531
00:38:12,499 --> 00:38:14,751
MS. MOON

532
00:38:15,502 --> 00:38:16,628
POWER OFF

533
00:38:31,476 --> 00:38:34,604
[operator] <i>The person</i>
<i>you're trying to reach is not available.</i>

534
00:38:34,687 --> 00:38:35,897
<i>Please leave a message…</i>

535
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:38,358
MS. KANG

536
00:38:47,575 --> 00:38:49,577
[indistinct chatter on TV]

537
00:38:59,671 --> 00:39:00,672
[Seok-jae] Ah, shit.

538
00:39:25,196 --> 00:39:26,114
[Seok-jae] The fuck?

539
00:39:26,614 --> 00:39:27,699
[Hyeon-nam grunts, pants]

540
00:39:30,827 --> 00:39:31,828
Get over there.

541
00:39:33,621 --> 00:39:35,081
What the fuck is this?

542
00:39:37,584 --> 00:39:39,627
Oh, you fucking bitch. Come here!

543
00:39:40,336 --> 00:39:42,797
Come here. Come on. God fucking damn it.

544
00:39:43,882 --> 00:39:45,550
-[panting]
-You bitch. You little…

545
00:39:46,634 --> 00:39:48,386
What is this? Where'd you get this?

546
00:39:49,053 --> 00:39:50,388
You said you don't have any money!

547
00:39:51,306 --> 00:39:53,433
It's not my money. I have to give it back.

548
00:39:54,267 --> 00:39:55,977
Don't give me
that fucking bullshit, bitch!

549
00:39:57,312 --> 00:39:59,731
Is Sun-a working somewhere?
Which bar is it?

550
00:40:01,024 --> 00:40:03,985
Damn it, this is all you got
for her so far? You're such an idiot!

551
00:40:04,068 --> 00:40:06,029
Sun-a's a child, she's only 14!

552
00:40:07,030 --> 00:40:08,615
-How could you even think that?
-Bullshit!

553
00:40:08,698 --> 00:40:09,699
[grunts]

554
00:40:09,782 --> 00:40:11,701
If she isn't, where is she, then?

555
00:40:13,494 --> 00:40:14,996
Some woman.

556
00:40:15,997 --> 00:40:19,751
She asked me
to send somebody a text with my phone.

557
00:40:20,460 --> 00:40:22,462
She said they knew her number already.

558
00:40:23,379 --> 00:40:25,548
And that she wanted to scare them.

559
00:40:26,549 --> 00:40:29,802
But then I read the text
and it just seemed so weird to me.

560
00:40:30,595 --> 00:40:31,596
I swear.

561
00:40:32,263 --> 00:40:33,431
-What did the text say?
-I…

562
00:40:34,015 --> 00:40:36,851
I'm gonna…
I'm just gonna give it all back.

563
00:40:36,935 --> 00:40:38,353
Please, let me give it back!

564
00:40:38,436 --> 00:40:40,355
God damn it, just answer my question!

565
00:40:41,439 --> 00:40:42,440
Show me the text.

566
00:40:44,067 --> 00:40:45,318
Where's your phone?

567
00:40:45,902 --> 00:40:47,403
[dramatic music playing]

568
00:40:48,404 --> 00:40:49,989
SEVEN MISSED CALLS
MA'AM

569
00:40:52,825 --> 00:40:54,202
I JUST NEED YOU TO SEND A TEXT

570
00:40:54,285 --> 00:40:55,119
I WON'T DO IT

571
00:40:55,203 --> 00:40:56,621
THINK ABOUT IT, IT'S GOOD MONEY

572
00:41:01,417 --> 00:41:02,418
[callous laughter]

573
00:41:09,092 --> 00:41:11,052
So this is what you've been up to, huh?

574
00:41:20,853 --> 00:41:21,854
[music trails off]

575
00:41:26,150 --> 00:41:26,985
Kim.

576
00:41:28,236 --> 00:41:30,989
Gyeong-ran.

577
00:41:32,365 --> 00:41:33,199
Huh?

578
00:41:36,035 --> 00:41:37,495
You have an "o" in your name.

579
00:41:38,746 --> 00:41:39,580
An "o"?

580
00:41:40,748 --> 00:41:42,166
[Yeon-jin's mother] <i>Did you forget?</i>

581
00:41:42,667 --> 00:41:44,043
<i>The shaman said you'd get bad luck…</i>

582
00:41:44,127 --> 00:41:45,420
MOON DONG-EUN

583
00:41:45,503 --> 00:41:46,963
<i>from people with O's in their name.</i>

584
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:48,881
[Yeon-jin] <i>Son Myeong-o.</i>

585
00:41:50,174 --> 00:41:51,342
[door opens]

586
00:41:51,426 --> 00:41:53,011
Ms. Park, we're ready for you.

587
00:41:53,094 --> 00:41:54,095
[Gyeong-ran] Okay.

588
00:41:55,805 --> 00:41:57,181
That's a nice pattern, right?

589
00:41:57,265 --> 00:41:58,933
-I really like this.
-It's so well made.

590
00:41:59,017 --> 00:42:00,018
Look, this one here.

591
00:42:00,101 --> 00:42:01,811
-Amazing.
-[phone chimes]

592
00:42:04,022 --> 00:42:05,148
[woman] Oh!

593
00:42:05,732 --> 00:42:06,941
Oh my gosh.

594
00:42:07,442 --> 00:42:10,361
[woman gasps] My God!
Wow! Look at this one.

595
00:42:10,445 --> 00:42:12,488
I KNOW THAT YOUR DAUGHTER
KILLED SOMEBODY

596
00:42:12,572 --> 00:42:15,408
[intricate, dramatic music playing]

597
00:42:19,579 --> 00:42:22,331
I KNOW THAT YOUR DAUGHTER
KILLED SOMEBODY

598
00:42:23,291 --> 00:42:24,417
[woman] What's wrong?

599
00:42:25,418 --> 00:42:27,587
Yeong-ae! Hey, Yeong-ae!

600
00:42:27,670 --> 00:42:29,338
Yeong-ae, what's wrong? Yeong-ae?

601
00:42:30,256 --> 00:42:31,257
[woman] Yeong-ae!

602
00:42:32,633 --> 00:42:34,010
Hey, Yeong-ae!

603
00:42:35,136 --> 00:42:36,220
Yeong-ae!

604
00:42:37,889 --> 00:42:39,348
Stop! What's wrong?

605
00:42:41,601 --> 00:42:43,311
Yeong-ae, stop!

606
00:42:48,357 --> 00:42:50,359
[dramatic music continuing]

607
00:42:55,865 --> 00:42:57,992
[Dong-eun] <i>Do you remember, Yeon-jin?</i>

608
00:42:58,951 --> 00:43:03,498
<i>Some time ago, you told your audience</i>
<i>to watch out for swells.</i>

609
00:43:03,581 --> 00:43:06,334
Swells will be flowing
into the East Sea for some time,

610
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:09,962
and in some places, high waves
will be going over the seashore rocks.

611
00:43:10,046 --> 00:43:11,798
A swell is mostly a receding wave,

612
00:43:11,881 --> 00:43:15,593
but can also be the most ferocious wave
seen in the entire ocean.

613
00:43:16,469 --> 00:43:19,180
[Dong-eun] <i>A swell can be</i>
<i>especially scary,</i>

614
00:43:19,263 --> 00:43:22,600
<i>because an accurate</i>
<i>forecasting method hasn't been developed,</i>

615
00:43:23,559 --> 00:43:25,603
<i>so it's incredibly hard to predict.</i>

616
00:43:26,604 --> 00:43:29,190
<i>And it can consume</i>
<i>everything in an instant,</i>

617
00:43:29,941 --> 00:43:31,734
<i>even if the water was calm,</i>

618
00:43:32,235 --> 00:43:33,236
<i>without ripples.</i>

619
00:43:39,742 --> 00:43:41,744
[dramatic music intensifying]

620
00:43:53,589 --> 00:43:56,259
[Dong-eun] <i>That day was</i>
<i>the first time Ms. Kang saw</i>

621
00:43:56,342 --> 00:43:59,303
<i>her face as she had never seen it before.</i>

622
00:44:00,054 --> 00:44:03,891
<i>For the first time,</i>
<i>she could see hope on her own face.</i>

623
00:44:05,518 --> 00:44:08,729
<i>But I don't think</i>
<i>that she was the only one</i>

624
00:44:09,522 --> 00:44:11,023
<i>who found hope that day.</i>

625
00:44:14,819 --> 00:44:16,988
FORENSIC DATA RECOVERY

626
00:44:19,282 --> 00:44:21,284
[giddy laughter]

627
00:44:35,923 --> 00:44:36,924
[Ye-sol] How do I look?

628
00:44:37,842 --> 00:44:40,219
Hey, this is green, right?

629
00:44:41,846 --> 00:44:43,514
There's a little red on them too.

630
00:44:44,223 --> 00:44:45,224
Where?

631
00:45:07,788 --> 00:45:08,789
[Yeong-jun] Here.

632
00:45:13,794 --> 00:45:16,088
[man] Aren't you supposed to be a cop?

633
00:45:17,256 --> 00:45:18,507
I am, yeah.

634
00:45:20,009 --> 00:45:22,511
But if all police officers
were just and had a sense of duty,

635
00:45:22,595 --> 00:45:24,013
then why would we need the law?

636
00:45:24,639 --> 00:45:27,808
My standards are rising now,
but I think I'm also out of luck.

637
00:45:29,977 --> 00:45:31,145
So keep an eye on it.

638
00:45:32,230 --> 00:45:33,898
That guy's my pension, all right?

639
00:45:33,981 --> 00:45:35,441
[man chuckles]

640
00:45:36,317 --> 00:45:38,069
Don't worry. I'll take care of him.

641
00:45:49,664 --> 00:45:51,290
[Yeo-jeong] Do you still feel sick?

642
00:45:54,168 --> 00:45:55,920
Maybe I drove too recklessly.

643
00:46:00,174 --> 00:46:01,592
I have a question.

644
00:46:04,345 --> 00:46:09,517
Before you even saw
the pictures up on my walls of them,

645
00:46:10,726 --> 00:46:12,353
you already knew about Myeong-o.

646
00:46:13,980 --> 00:46:15,398
Why didn't you tell me?

647
00:46:16,065 --> 00:46:17,817
Why didn't you ask me anything?

648
00:46:18,442 --> 00:46:19,902
Did you think I killed him?

649
00:46:25,283 --> 00:46:29,036
Executioners don't question those above.

650
00:46:30,162 --> 00:46:31,998
It all comes to the same conclusion.

651
00:46:32,999 --> 00:46:36,585
I don't care if you killed him,
and I don't care if you didn't kill him.

652
00:46:37,795 --> 00:46:40,631
Whether you want a corpse
or the evidence destroyed,

653
00:46:41,465 --> 00:46:43,634
I'm here to do whatever you want.

654
00:46:47,013 --> 00:46:48,681
Who am I to you?

655
00:46:48,764 --> 00:46:51,434
Why do you want to do this for me?
What makes you so sure?

656
00:46:51,517 --> 00:46:53,894
This is so much deeper than "sure."

657
00:46:55,813 --> 00:46:57,648
I've already told you before.

658
00:46:58,482 --> 00:47:00,776
I had a very rough period of my life.

659
00:47:02,862 --> 00:47:04,572
And I realized when I tutored you…

660
00:47:05,239 --> 00:47:07,658
"Oh, this woman…"

661
00:47:08,492 --> 00:47:09,660
"She can save me."

662
00:47:10,161 --> 00:47:12,163
[sweeping, emotional music playing]

663
00:47:15,666 --> 00:47:19,754
Well, at some point, we all get to choose
what kind of person we'll become.

664
00:47:20,921 --> 00:47:24,508
I've chosen to become
the one who's your partner in crime.

665
00:47:25,926 --> 00:47:27,178
It suits me as well.

666
00:47:31,891 --> 00:47:33,642
Anyone ever tell you you're crazy?

667
00:47:34,226 --> 00:47:35,603
As crazy as you need.

668
00:47:37,355 --> 00:47:38,439
Will you let me?

669
00:47:44,612 --> 00:47:46,947
[Dong-eun] <i>I wonder</i>
<i>which one of us will cause</i>

670
00:47:47,031 --> 00:47:50,076
<i>an unpredictable swell</i>
<i>with our hope, Yeon-jin.</i>

671
00:48:02,171 --> 00:48:04,173
[tense, dramatic music playing]

672
00:48:31,700 --> 00:48:32,993
YEONGSAN FUNERAL HOME

673
00:48:33,077 --> 00:48:34,745
[man] Hello! Welcome.

674
00:48:51,762 --> 00:48:53,764
[dark, brooding outro music playing]
